            <abstract>
                <p>  A Miniature showing  the 
                    <persName ref="PRS11288AnAzMi"> three Hebrew youths </persName>
                   thrown into a fiery furnace. The miniature generally includes the angel,
                    <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/>, who protects them from the flames.
                    The miniature may also feature <persName ref="PRS11373Nebuc">Nebuchadnezzar</persName> and his guards.
                    From the seventeenth-century the episode may be divided into several scenes.
                    
                    The main typologies attested in the Ethiopian tradition are:
                    <list>
                        <item>Type 1 <desc>The Angel stands behind the youths</desc> </item>
                        <item>Type 2 <desc>The Angel stands to the side of the youths</desc> </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
